Overview of noun spectacle

The noun spectacle has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (8) spectacle -- (something or someone seen (especially a notable or unusual sight); "the tragic spectacle of cripples trying to escape")
2. (2) spectacle -- (an elaborate and remarkable display on a lavish scale)
3. spectacle -- (a blunder that makes you look ridiculous; used in the phrase `make a spectacle of' yourself)
